17/10/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan arrived Thursday (16 October) in Brussels, where he will represent his country at the EU Summit and Intergovernmental Conference.
Accompanying Erdogan are Turkish State Ministers Ali Babacan and Mehmet Aydin.
Turkey will assume an observer status during the first part of the summit, when the draft constitution is discussed.
(Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 16/10/03)
